This hook enables a peer review process to be integrated into a project banner. It should be attached to the {{para|HOOK_NOTE}} hook. The following parameters are used:

*<code>'''category'''</code> ''(Required)'' &ndash; the 'category' parameter ''must'' be passed through the template to enable category optout. {{nowrap|''Eg: '''<code><nowiki>category={{{category|¬}}}</nowiki></code>'''''}}
*<code>'''peer review'''</code> ''(Required)'' &ndash; the parameter that will trigger the active peer review note; should be passed through. {{nowrap|''Eg: '''<code><nowiki>peer review={{{peer-review|}}}</nowiki></code>'''''}}
*<code>'''old peer review'''</code> ''(Required)'' &ndash; the parameter that will trigger the old peer review note; should be passed through. {{nowrap|''Eg: '''<code><nowiki>old peer review={{{old-peer-review|}}}</nowiki></code>'''''}}
*<code>'''LINK'''</code> ''(Required)'' &ndash; the full link to where the review for this particular article is held. {{nowrap|''Eg: '''<code><nowiki>Wikipedia:WikiProject Tulips/Assessment</nowiki></code>'''''}}
*<code>'''IMAGE'''</code> &ndash; the name of the image to use. If not specified then [[File:Exquisite-kfind.png|30px]] is used.
*<code>'''CAT'''</code> &ndash; if defined, pages using {{para|peer review|yes}} will be categorised into this category. {{nowrap|''Eg: '''<code><nowiki>Requests for Tulips peer review</nowiki></code>''' → [[:Category:Requests for Tulips peer review]]''}}
*<code>'''OLD_CAT'''</code> &ndash; if defined, pages using {{para|old peer review|yes}} will be categorised into this category. {{nowrap|''Eg: '''<code><nowiki>Old requests for Tulips peer review</nowiki></code>''' → [[:Category:Old requests for Tulips peer review]]''}}
*<code>'''title'''</code> → If the page has been moved since it was reviewed, specify the old page title (the one the review was archived under) to make the link point correctly to the review.
*<code>'''INVALID_CAT'''</code>  &ndash; if defined, pages using {{para|peer review|yes}} without a valid peer review page existing be categorised into this category.